msIdentifier.collection: Hampton L. Carson Collection on the Growth and Development of the Common Law

msContents.summary: This manuscript contains the Statuta vetera (Old Statutes).

msItem.title: Statuta vetera, including the Magna Carta, Carta de Foresta, Statutum de Merton, Statuta de Marlebergh, Statuta de Westminster I, Statuta de Gloucester, Explanationes Gloucester, Statuta de Westminster II, Statuta de Westminster III, Statutum de Religioses, and the Statue of Lincoln (February 14, 1301)

supportDesc.extent: iii+167+iii; 85 x 48 mm bound to 92 x 55 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto

collation.p: The binding is quite tight; appears to have been gathered in quires of 8

layoutDesc.layout: Frame-ruled in lead point in one column of 26 lines; fols. 1r-4v, 13r-17v, and 152v-167v have been left blank; written area: 65 x 36 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: One historiated initial; illuminated initials and borders throughout; paragraph signs in red and blue
Inside front coverBookplate, Free Library of Philadelphia, gift of Hampton L. Carson

binding.p: Late 19th century red morocco biding; gilt edges; stamped in gold on spine: "MAGNA CARTA MS SAEC. XIII."

history.provenance: John Dewey (?); Hampton L. Carson, Philadelphia; given to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1929; "John Dewey" written in pencil on fol. 155r in a late eighteenth century or early nineteenth century hand. Bookplate of the Philadelphia Free Library, gift of Hampton L. Carson pasted onto inside of front cover
